                  <provenance>The name of the original donor was erased
                     throughout the Ms. and replaced with those of Walda Hāymānot, Za-Walda Māryām
                     or ʿArkä Śǝllāse (e.g., <locus target="#19vb">19vb</locus>, 43vb), which in
                     turn have been sometimes erased or crossed out and replaced with those of
                     Tawalda Madḫǝn and his wife Walatta Yoḥannǝs (e.g., <locus target="#13ra">13ra</locus>, 38ra, 39va, 62rb, 63vb).
 According to Additiones 1 and 2
                     the Ms. has been purchased and donated to the church by bašša Bǝrru whose
                     baptismal name was Tawalda Madḫǝn.</provenance>
               </history>
